  <static seed="106" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Each page of a book consists of a header, a footer and the middle part. The header is <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> inches in height; the footer is <m>{{\frac{11}{12}}}</m> inches in height; and the middle part is <m>{4{\textstyle\frac{1}{6}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
<p>What is the total height of each page in this book? Use mixed number in your answer if needed.</p>
<p>Each page in this book is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> inches in height.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We add up the height of the header, middle part and footer to find the total height of a page:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{6}}} + {4{\textstyle\frac{1}{6}}} + {{\frac{11}{12}}}
      \amp =    {{\frac{1}{6}}} + 4 + {{\frac{1}{6}}} + {{\frac{11}{12}}} \\
      \amp =    4 + {{\frac{1}{6}}} + {{\frac{1}{6}}} + {{\frac{11}{12}}} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{1\cdot2}{6\cdot2} + \frac{1\cdot2}{6\cdot2} + \frac{11}{12}  \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{2}{12} +  \frac{2}{12} + \frac{11}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{2+2+11}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{15}{12} \\
      \amp = 4 + \frac{5}{4} \\
      \amp = 4 + 1 \frac{1}{4} \\
      \amp = {5{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Each page in this book is <m>{5{\textstyle\frac{1}{4}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
</solution>
